overview: The user initiated a project to develop a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a Statement of Work. The primary goal was to integrate
  a database for storing questionnaire responses, implement a simple admin
  dashboard for data access, and establish necessary authentication middleware.
  After evaluating the existing codebase, it was determined that a database for
  responses, CSV export, and an admin dashboard with authentication were
  missing. Key decisions included using NeonDB for the database, implementing a
  simple password-based authentication via an environment variable, and
  combining demographic data fields to include year of birth, sex, zip code,
  weight, and height. The plan outlines the creation of a
   Prisma model, new API routes for data handling, and
  the development of an admin login and dashboard. The initial phase of
  implementation has begun with updates to the demographics section in the
  codebase.
